   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>In the navigation pane, expand<uicontrol>Documents</uicontrol>, and then click the required document folder.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the documents list page, select the appropriate document, and then click<uicontrol>View</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>Alternatively, double-click theappropriate document in the list.
                </p>
            <p>The document is opened onthe<uicontrol>VIEWER</uicontrol>page.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>If the document file type is mapped to a viewer that supports 2D and 3D drawings, then to switch the view between 2D and 3D, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>In the<uicontrol>VIEWER</uicontrol>page, click<image href="../../../Icons/FV-image3.png" placement="inline">
                        <alt>Document Browser</alt>
                     </image>on the toolbar.</p>
                  <p>The<uicontrol>Document Browser</uicontrol>dialog box is displayed.
                        </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>In the<uicontrol>Tree</uicontrol>tab, expand<uicontrol>Model</uicontrol>and then click the appropriate view.</p>
                  <p>
                     <note> If the document supports only 2D view, then the 3D view option is not available.You can view and examine a 2D or 3D drawing design in detail using the viewer tools.<ph product="Exclude_PG_Content">For information on using the 2D and 3D viewer tools, refer to<xref href="../Using2D3DTools.xml">Using 2D and 3D Viewer Tools</xref>.</ph>
                     </note>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
      </ol>
